Good day - here’s a couple of changes I have made over the last 6 months:

1. Walk bare feet where possible - and bought vivobarefoot for daily use. Benefit: knees and ankle more aligned and feet are stronger. Added benefit folks think you are strange!
2. Sleep with a mouth tape to encourage nose breathing!
👇

Contd.. 
After 4 weeks didn’t need tape anymore as naturally breathing through nose. Benefits: quality of sleep much better, wake up calmer and better rested
3. Pure cotton underwear - your balls deserve to  breathe and not be restricted 
4. Cut out seed oils from diet.

5. Exercise: Olympic weightlifting training 3 times and 1 to 2 squash games a week. Benefit improved sleep after working, endorphin released immediately after exercise, improved brain function (better focus and stress management)
6. Stopped drinking tap water, reduce plastic bottle usage - installed RO water filter.

7. Sleep for at least 7 hours every night - this probably has had the biggest impact overall.
8. Stress - this is the one big exception that I have not been able to resolve - mostly work related and with also wanting to progress faster than I’m currently - any advice or tips welcome
